@node Introduction "Zuppel Guide  -  Introduction"
@TOC Main

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

Zuppel is a program to search words in a file. One could think of it as
a GREP utility with a GUI, but with different search options.
The idea was born when I found a huge wordlist on the internet and my mom
was wasting her time searching for words in dictionairies for completing
crossword puzzles.
The basic idea is that you enter a search pattern and Zuppel will come up
with all words matching your pattern.

Easy puzzling from now on!


If you use this program for something else, please contact @{" Me " LINK Author}!


Let's see what the @{" System requirements " LINK Requirements} are..
@endnode


@node Requirements "Zuppel Guide  -  Requirements"
@TOC Main

@{b}Requirements@{ub}

Zuppel requires at least OS2.04, I think ;)




Let's go on to the @{" Installation " LINK Installation}
@endnode

@node Installation "Zuppel Guide  -  Installation"
@TOC Main

@{b}Installation@{ub}

Installation is very easy. Just drag the Zuppel drawer to the disk or
drawer you want. Life is easy when you know how!




Now it's installed, let me explain the @{" Usage " LINK Usage}.

@endnode

@NODE Usage  "Zuppel Guide  -  Usage"
@TOC Main

@{b}Usage@{ub}

Let me give you a possible procedure to use this program.
First choose a wordlist. Then enter a search pattern and choose a Search-
mode. If you expect many matches set the Expect gadget to Many, else set
it to Few. Then the chosen wordlist is searched with the given search
pattern. All matches are stored in the Search results listview.


This is the main window of Zuppel. Click on the gadgets to find out
what they're for!

